cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR

This paper discusses the management of spectrum resources in cellular networks, specifically in HetNets (heterogeneous networks). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes auction-based solutions for dynamic spectrum resource sharing, which involves game theory and mechanism design, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions simulation results that involve multimedia traffic, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential security risks of in-band relaying, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category.
